      <div style="text-align: left; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;">&#160;Item 2.02 &#8211; Results of Operations and Financial Condition.</div>

      <div style="font-size: 10pt;">&#160;</div>

      <div style="text-align: left; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 10pt; text-indent: 36pt;">The information set forth under Item 7.01 of this Form 8-K is incorporated herein by reference.</div>

      <div style="font-size: 10pt;"><br />
      </div>

      <div style="text-align: left; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 10pt; text-indent: 36pt;">The information set forth in Item 2.02 of this Form 8-K (including Exhibit 99.1) shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section 18 of the
        Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), or otherwise subject to the liabilities under that Section. Furthermore, such information shall not be deemed to be incorporated by reference into any filing under the Securities Act
        of 1933, as amended (the &#8220;Securities Act&#8221;), or the Exchange Act, except as shall be expressly set forth by specific reference in such a filing.</div>

      <div style="font-size: 10pt;"><br />
      </div>

      <div style="text-align: left; font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;">Item 7.01 &#8211; Regulation FD Disclosure.</div>

      <div style="font-size: 10pt;"><br />
      </div>

      <div>
        <div style="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 10pt; text-indent: 36pt;">
          <div>
            <div style="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 10pt; text-indent: 36pt;">On November 30, 2022, AngioDynamics, Inc. (&#8220;AngioDynamics&#8221; or the &#8220;Company&#8221;) will present at the 2022 Piper Sandler
              Healthcare Conference.&#160; The presentation slides are furnished herewith as Exhibit 99.1.&#160; Management expects cash at the end of the second fiscal quarter, ended November 30, 2022, to be approximately $28 &#8211; $30 million; an increase in net cash
              from the end of the first fiscal quarter of approximately $3.5 &#8211;$5.5 million. This expectation does not include the $4.2 million receivable related to the CARES Act.</div>

            <div><br />
            </div>

            <div style="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 10pt; text-indent: 36pt;">The Company expects to report results for its second fiscal quarter ended November 30, 2022, on or around January 5,
              2023, in accordance with its typical schedule.</div>

          </div>

        </div>

        <div style="font-size: 10pt;"><br />
        </div>

        <div style="text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 'Times New Roman'; font-size: 10pt; text-indent: 36pt;">The presentation slides furnished pursuant to Item 7.01 of this Form 8-K (including Exhibit 99.1) shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221;
          for purposes of Section 18 of the Exchange Act, or otherwise subject to the liabilities under that Section. Furthermore, the presentation slides shall not be deemed to be incorporated by reference into any filing under the Securities Act or the
          Exchange Act.</div>

      </div>

          All statements regarding AngioDynamics&#8217; expected future financial position, results of operations, cash flows, business strategy, budgets, projected costs, capital expenditures, products, competitive positions, growth opportunities, plans and
          objectives of management for future operations, as well as statements that include the words such as &#8220;expects,&#8221; &#8220;reaffirms,&#8221; &#8220;intends,&#8221; &#8220;anticipates,&#8221; &#8220;plans,&#8221; &#8220;believes,&#8221; &#8220;seeks,&#8221; &#8220;estimates,&#8221; &#8220;projects&#8221;, &#8220;optimistic,&#8221; or variations of such

          materially from AngioDynamics&#8217; expectations, expressed or implied. Factors that may affect the actual results achieved by AngioDynamics include, without limitation, the scale and scope of the COVID-19 global pandemic, the ability of AngioDynamics
          to develop its existing and new products, technological advances and patents attained by competitors, infringement of AngioDynamics&#8217; technology or assertions that AngioDynamics&#8217; technology infringes the technology of third parties, the ability of
          AngioDynamics to effectively compete against competitors that have substantially greater resources, future actions by the FDA or other regulatory agencies, domestic and foreign health care reforms and government regulations, results of pending or
          future clinical trials, overall economic conditions (including inflation, labor shortages and supply chain challenges including the cost and availability of raw materials), the results of on-going litigation, challenges with respect to
          third-party distributors or joint venture partners or collaborators, the results of sales efforts, the effects of product recalls and product liability claims, changes in key personnel, the ability of AngioDynamics to execute on strategic
          initiatives, the effects of economic, credit and capital market conditions, general market conditions, market acceptance, foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations, the effects on pricing from group purchasing organizations and competition, the

          <div style="text-align: left;" class="slideTextFrame"><font style="color: white; display: inline; font-family: '\'Times New Roman\'', Times, serif; font-size: 1pt;">&#160;7&#160;&#160;Peripheral Atherectomy&#160;&#160;2.35 mm&#160;&#160;Aspiration and Off-Center capabilities and
              indicated for Peripheral Atherectomy and In-Stent Restenosis (ISR)&#160;&#160;2.0 mm&#160;&#160;Aspiration capability and indicated for Peripheral Atherectomy and ISR&#160;&#160;1.5 mm&#160;&#160;Indicated for Peripheral Atherectomy&#160;&#160;0.9 mm&#160;&#160;Indicated for Peripheral
              Atherectomy&#160;&#160;$760M&#160;&#160;Source: Peripheral Vascular Devices Medtech 360 Market Analysis US December, 2021. Millennium Research Group, Inc.&#160;&#160;7&#160;&#160;2022 Served Market&#160;&#160;Above the Knee (ATK)&#160;&#160;Below the Knee (BTK)&#160;&#160;Office Based Lab (OBL)&#160;&#160;Hospital&#160;&#160;Why
              wavelength matters&#160;&#160;Each type of tissue interacts differently with a given wavelength&#160;&#160;The Auryon System produces a photon energy of 3.5eV, which is low enough to be nonreactive to vessel endothelium, but high enough to vaporize
              calcium.1,2&#160;&#160;Why pulse width and amplitude matter&#160;&#160;Greater amplitude is achieved with shorter pulses, which can deposit energy before thermal diffusion occurs.&#160;&#160;The Auryon System has a pulse width of 10 to 25ns, ensuring enough power to
              target the lesion and spare the vessel.3&#160;&#160;1. Herzog A, Bogdan S, Glikson M, Ishaaya AA, Love C. Selective tissue ablation using laser radiation at 355 nm in lead extraction by a hybrid catheter; a preliminary report. Lasers Surg Med.
              2016;48(3):281-287.&#160;&#160;2. Spectranetics Corporation. CVX-300 Excimer Laser System: Operator&#8217;s Manual. Version 28. 2019:1-56.&#160;&#160;3. Auryon. Instructions for use. AngioDynamics; 2019. &#160;</font></div>

              pulses between probes, NanoKnife destroys cells without relying on extreme heat or cold &#160;&#160;Why this is different?&#160;&#160;This patented technology facilitates functional tissue regeneration post ablation and spares vital structures within the
              ablation zone&#160;&#160;Approximately &#160;&#160;100,000 &#160;&#160;men are estimated to be candidates for focal therapy each year8&#160;&#160;Effectively destroys targeted tissue with precise treatment margins5 &#160;&#160;Spares vital structures within the ablation zone6 &#160;&#160;Enables

if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
